      "id": 663,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:3",
      "content": "Two changes to `src/index.ts`:\n\n## 1. New `synapse update` command\n\nCurrently `synapse init --update` re-applies templates and refreshes CLAUDE.md. Split this into a standalone `synapse update [path]` command.\n\n- Add a new Commander command `update [path]` with the same description as the flag: \"re-apply latest templates and refresh CLAUDE.md in an existing project\"\n- It should call `synapseInit(resolvedPath, true)` (the `update=true` path), same as the existing `--update` branch in the `init` handler\n- Keep the `--update` / `-u` flag on `init` as well for backwards compatibility (or remove it — your call, but if you remove it, note it)\n- The `path` argument should default to `process.cwd()` same as `init`\n\nKey reference: the `init` command handler is around line 185–228 in `src/index.ts`. The `synapseInit` function is lines 71–184.\n\n## 2. `synapse start` opens the dashboard URL in the browser\n\nAfter the dashboard starts (after `startDashboard(port)` is called, around line 350), open the URL in the default browser.\n\n- Use Node's built-in approach: `import { exec } from 'child_process'` (already imported as `execSync`/`spawnSync` — use `exec` or `execSync` with the right command)\n- Cross-platform open: `open` on macOS, `xdg-open` on Linux, `start` on Windows. Use `process.platform` to pick the right one. A simple helper is fine.\n- Open `http://localhost:${port}` (the same URL already printed to stderr)\n- Do this only once, non-blocking — don't wait for it to complete\n\n## Key file\n- `src/index.ts` — all changes are here\n\nAfter implementing, run `npm run build` (or `tsc`) to verify it compiles clean, then call `report_done` with a summary.",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780689587187,
      "read_at": 1780689590242,
